        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Follow The FFXIV Fan Festival 2026 Keynote's Latest Announcements Here -- Live Blog]]></title>
            <link>https://www.mmorpg.com/event-blogs/follow-the-ffxiv-fan-festival-2026-keynotes-latest-announcements-here-live-blog-2000137891</link>
            <guid>1500982</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><article>
            
                
                        
            <header>
            
                <h2>Tracking FanFest's biggest announcements and updates</h2>
                     
            <p><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> <i></i> Updated: <time datetime="2026-04-24T17:28:26+00:00">Apr 24, 2026 1:28 PM</time>  <i></i> Posted: <time datetime="2026-04-24T16:30:00+00:00">Apr 24, 2026 12:30 PM ET</time><br><i></i> Category: </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/final-fantasy-xiv/event-blogs" rel="nofollow">Event Blogs</a><span> </span><a href="#comments" vanilla-identifier="news_137891">0</a></p>
            </header> 
            
        <!--<div class="sharethis-inline-share-buttons" style="min-height: 32px;"></div>-->
    
            <section>
            
                    
                        

            <div><p><span>Today, at the <a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/final-fantasy-xiv" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Final Fantasy 14 Fan Festival</a> taking place in Anaheim, the game’s director and executive producer Naoki Yoshida will be giving the highly-anticipated Keynote presentation that unveils the event’s biggest announcement pertaining to the game. Starting at <strong>10:00 a.m. PDT, and going for approximately 2 hours and 15 minutes,</strong> the Keynote presentation at FFXIV FanFest is slated to give an idea of what’s to come in the popular MMORPG. In past years, this has been a general overview of what’s to come in the next expansion.&nbsp;</span></p>

                
                    
                        

		
		
		
		
		
		
				
		
		

		

		
		
		
		
		
		
		
                    
                
            
<p><span>However, without a patch overview and other future development panels penciled into the main event, chances are very high we’ll also see what’s in store for the rest of </span><em><span>Dawntrail</span></em><span>—and possibly even in </span><em><span>FFXIV</span></em><span> beyond the upcoming expansion. For instance, players are looking to hear more about what the upcoming endgame Ultimate raid is, given a Kefka-themed teaser at the end of the trailer.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><iframe width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" title="YouTube video player" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" data-cookieblock-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_aCGzxWczCM?si=7vLbu6lZE9FWxg8D" data-cookieconsent="preferences,statistics,marketing"></iframe></p>
<p><span>What are you looking forward to—or what do you think is coming in <em>FFXIV's</em> future?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><em><span>To catch up on updates from the beginning of the presentation, be sure to start at the bottom of the page—the newest updates will appear as they come from the top.&nbsp;</span></em></p>
<p><iframe width="620" height="378" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" src="https://player.twitch.tv/?channel=finalfantasyxiv&amp;parent=www.mmorpg.com" scrolling="no"></iframe></p></div> 
            
                        
            
                

        
        

        
        
        
        <div id="live-updates">
                    
            <figure id="update-730">
                
                <blockquote><p>As they promised a few Live Letters ago, they're looking at adding more dynamic content into content areas. This is something that they said is part of the changes they wanted to do in the wake of improving server data systems, so this should be exciting, and I guess to the point they also mention they're trying to make sure it's stable.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;They acknowledge that the quests are an important part of the system, and that this is getting a look-over... <em>more in Berlin</em>.&nbsp;</p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-729">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 6:09 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>While these changes shown are arriving in 8.0, there'll be more updates to character creation coming throughout the 8.0 expansion's patch series. (Or Seasons, I guess.)</p>
<p><em>(Also this is where our stream of screenshots end - everyone say thank you, Joseph.)</em></p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-727">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 6:08 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>They're overhauling the Armoury System, which already gets a big cheer.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The big change getting even bigger cheers is that top-level gear will be able to be "merged" over into other classes that are at that level, which means that players will have to grind less in order to help their friends (or their less competent statics) (or Party Finder).&nbsp;</p>
<p>"Character Action Skins" are coming, which appear to be effectively equippable actions and animations.&nbsp;</p>
<p>...more to come in Berlin, we guess!</p>

</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-728">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 6:07 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>A ton of character customization updates are changing which gets a cheer so loud my ears rang for a second.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The big thing they're emphasizing on is the color selection tool, which will let players pick from a full color spectrum instead of just pre-selected colors.&nbsp;</p>
<p>There'll also be iris and lip customization, face paint layering and toggling of gear pieces.&nbsp;</p>


</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-726">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:57 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>This next part goes into how aesthetically-focused many&nbsp;<em>FFXIV</em> fans appear to be. Therefore, in the Adventurer Activity screen, characters will be fully posable, and the backgrounds will be interchangeable.&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-725">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:55 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>They're introducing "Seasons" - which is basically a way to distinguish patch cycle time frames, as they explain it, instead of saying Patch Number-Dot-Number.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The patch Seasons will be grouped in twos, based on standard patch cycles where Item Level goes up.</p>
<p>It makes sense: as it stands, item level bumps come with the standard Raids that come in "even" patches.&nbsp;</p>

</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-724">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:50 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>The next change coming is how to increase Item Level - which requires players to literally get new items, which can be a slog.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Great news: They're changing this.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Bad news: They're telling us at Tokyo FanFest in late October.&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>(You know what? This is a fair system to fine-tune.)</em></p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-723">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:48 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>Players will be able to do activities each week that earn Activity Points, varying by activities, which players can then spend to pick up rewards.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Some missions, like the Main Scenario Quest roulette - one of the most "efficient" roulette systems today - can only be done once per week, but others can be repeated for more points. (Roulettes only let you do these activities once per day, generally.) Players are encouraged to do activities that firt their play style.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Also under consideration is a system that lets you "back-earn" points from the prior week.&nbsp;</p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-722">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:44 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>The first thing introduced is the Adventurer Activity reward system - which brings daily and weekly tasks to tackle.&nbsp;</p>
<p>As it stands, in order to max out your various currency, you need to do a bunch of Roulettes of various types.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>Now, instead of requiring all of these Roulettes, the Adventurer Activity system will streamline rewarsds to remove some of the monotony and free up time.&nbsp;</p>
<p>(This is an early mock-up of the system, and they note it's subject to change.)&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-721">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:41 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>How big are the overhauls? So big, they'll need to cover it over three FanFests...</p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-720">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:37 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>We're getting an entire section, as usual, about design updates that'll be coming on XIV. They do point out that they are, in fact, putting special emphasis on this section.&nbsp;</p>
<p>It's pointed out that XIV has indeed been around since 2010 - 2012 if you count just <em>A Realm Reborn</em> - and a lot has changed...&nbsp;</p>
<p>And while there's something comforting about a classic vibe, change is good, and they explain that things do get fatiguing.&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-719">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:31 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>Without further commentary.&nbsp;</p>

</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-718">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:30 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>We're getting some concept art from the new areas, as well as a glimpse at "Arcane Giants" roaming the Fourth that we'll learn more about soon.&nbsp;</p>


<p>And some towns, specifically, which the crowd seems to be eating up:&nbsp;</p>



</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-717">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:23 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>We're getting some neat previews of the Fourth, where it seems like they're taking liberties regarding the designs since they can start fresh - and they're really going hard on it.</p>
<p>Anyone have any thoughts about possible influences from past FF titles?&nbsp;</p>



<p>This above image is supposedly a lighting test for this area.&nbsp;</p>

</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-716">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:18 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>We've been realm-hopping a bit, and this time, our destination is the Fourth reflection of the Source/Hydaelyn/Etheryis that's falling. We'll be meeting the "Wanderer" among, it seems, others.&nbsp;</p>
<p>But that's all they'll say, as next week's <a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/news/beastmaster-and-more-gameplay-shown-off-in-ffxivs-latest-live-letter-for-75-patches-2000137835" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Patch 7.5</a> will get more into it. Sounds like "Trail to the Heavens" may be aptly named.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-715">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:14 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>Naoki Yoshida confidently claims that&nbsp;<em>Evercold</em> will be coming to&nbsp;<em>FFXIV</em> in&nbsp;<strong>January 2027.</strong></p>
<p>"Nine months... is that enough?"&nbsp;</p>
<p>"I officially give you permission to:&nbsp;<em>Please, look forward to it.</em>"&nbsp;</p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-714">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:11 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>It seems our Warrior of Light for the <em>Evercold</em> expansion is a Reaper - and our new mutli-expansion "arc" is called the <strong>Godless Realms Saga</strong>. Without going into&nbsp;<em>Endwalker </em>spoiler details, it's technically fitting.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>            
            </figure>            
                    
            <figure id="update-713">
                <figcaption><span><i></i> </span><a href="https://www.mmorpg.com/profile/riningear">Victoria Rose</a><span> @ Apr 24, 2026 5:08 PM</span></figcaption>
                <blockquote><p>Welcome to FFXIV FanFest 2026! We're starting off strong with the trailer for the new expansion:&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Evercold!&nbsp;</h2>
<p>The new trailer seems to imply we'll be heading into the depths of the cold to discover secrets of eld that might unite the stars.&nbsp;</p>
<p>(Also, it's very loud in here, so we encourage you to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dk3rfUC80DE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">watch the trailer at home.)</a></p></blockquote>            
            </figure>            
        
        </div>

        
            
        

        
        

        
                    
        
        
    
            

            

            
            
                    
            
            

            </section>
            
                        
